column5: I'm looking for a little information about Taylors Cove from anyone that has stayed there. They don't have a website and don't want to book a week with them without knowing a little about the camp. Any information will be helpful. Thanks, Dog
I found this:http://www.practical-fishing-tips.com/taylors-cove.htmlI have driven by many times but have not stopped to check it out.

I haven't been to Taylor's Cove since they closed their campground, but was a frequent visitor prior to that. Ed Taylor is a standup guy who runs a nice operation. The location is in the dead center of many Rainy fishing opportunities. Swell Bay - Seine Bay - Baseline Bay - Red Gut and all the intersecting waters. Great walleye action all summer. Smallmouth fishing is excellent from late May through June.. Good crappie action in late May and June. I don't think you will be disappointed with this resort.
JDP and Baseline thanks for the info. Dog
